Quote:  Sherwin expressed an opinion as to what kind of novel it was. `It's pretty solid,' he said, `you'll have to take your coat off to read it.'... Counsel acknowledged that he didn't think that the expression `take your coat off' referred to immorality. Crown Prosecutor Russell: `It is a very hearty expression.'
